This paper deals with explaining the classification decisions of neural networks, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the issue of adversarial attacks, which is a security concern in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and cryptography (cs.CR). Additionally, the proposed method involves numerical analysis and optimization, which are relevant to numerical analysis (cs.NA) and neural networks (cs.NE).
